{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}Url Decode Filter - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Url Decode Filter</h1>

<p>Decodes a URL-encoded string.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ value | url_decode }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Examples</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ "hello+world" | url_decode }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> hello world</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ "foo%3Dbar%26baz%3Dqux" | url_decode }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> foo=bar&amp;baz=qux</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ "user%40example.com" | url_decode }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> user@example.com</p>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<p>Uses Go's <code>url.QueryUnescape</code>, which decodes both percent-encoded sequences and <code>+</code> as a space. If the string cannot be decoded (e.g. malformed percent sequences), the original string is returned unchanged.</p>

<h2>See Also</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/url_encode">url_encode</a></li>
</ul>
{% end %}
